== Semi-protected edit request on 7 February 2026 ==

{{edit semi-protected|British Isles|answered=yes}}
Change British Isles to Atlantic Archipelago. The term 'British Isles' is heavily outdated and is not the official name for the islands, it is not even used by the Government. [[User:Crafferty1119|Crafferty1119]] ([[User talk:Crafferty1119|talk]]) 11:19, 7 February 2026 (UTC)

:{{Not done}}''':''' please provide [[Wikipedia:Reliable sources|reliable sources]] that support the change you want made.<!-- Template:ESp --> &#123;&#123;[[User:GearsDatapack|GearsDatapack]]&#124;[[User talk:GearsDatapack|talk]]&#124;[[Special:Contributions/GearsDatapack|contribs]]&#125;&#125; 11:36, 7 February 2026 (UTC)
::[https://www.oireachtas.ie/en/debates/question/2005-09-28/495/]
::It also says on the wikipedia page itself.
::If you also look at the Good Friday Agreement, both the Irish and British Government refer to the islands as 'These Isles'[https://www.caughtbytheriver.net/2019/04/the-atlantic-archipelago/] [[Special:Contributions/&#126;2026-83632-5|&#126;2026-83632-5]] ([[User talk:&#126;2026-83632-5|talk]]) 11:43, 7 February 2026 (UTC)
:::Please see [[Talk:British_Isles/name_debate]], per the banner at the top of the page. &#123;&#123;[[User:GearsDatapack|GearsDatapack]]&#124;[[User talk:GearsDatapack|talk]]&#124;[[Special:Contributions/GearsDatapack|contribs]]&#125;&#125; 11:48, 7 February 2026 (UTC)
